  "text": "The present study has shown that teeth with fluorosis exhibit higher enamel fluoride content than sound teeth at depths up to 90 μm below the anatomical surface and regardless of fluorosis severity. There was a clear trend for teeth with increasing fluorosis severities exhibiting higher fluoride content, and especially for the outermost enamel layer, although not all comparisons were of statistical significance. These findings are in agreement with previous investigations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and highlight that excess systemic fluoride can be incorporated into the dental hard tissues.",
